          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A CD2 target with a thickness of 300 mu-g/cm2 was",
                "placed inside the HELIOS spectrometer"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Solenoid spectrometer HELIOS with 2 T",
                "magnetic field"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SI",
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The heavy-ion recoil particles",
                "identified using quadrant silicon dE-E recoil",
                "detectors placed at 500 mm downstream of the target",
                "position. Their dimensions were 10 mm inner radius",
                "and a 50 mm outer radius, placed 10 mm apart. The",
                "thickness of the dE and E detectors was 500 and 1000",
                "mu-m, respectively."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The light charged particles were detected using",
                "a position sensitive Si-detector array with the first",
                "active area beginning at 710 mm downstream of the",
                "target position. The array had six sides in a",
                "hexagonal shape with five detectors on each side. The",
                "position was determined by resistive charge division",
                "along the beam direction: the active area was 50 mm",
                " (along the beam axis) x 10 mm with a position",
                "resolution of roughly 1 mm along the beam axis."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Inverse kinematics was used"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The 16N secondary beam was produced from a 15N",
                "primary beam at 13.5 MeV/u bombarding a cryogenically",
                "cooled (90 K) deuterium gas cell at 1400 mbar. The",
                "total intensity of the 16N secondary beam (ground",
                "state and isomeric state) was 2E+5 pps at an energy",
                "of 11.8 MeV/u. Separate experiment was carried out to",
                "determine 16mN content of the beam. It was determined",
                "that the 16mN was (24+-2) % of the 16N beam, which was",
                "more than 50% of the total beam."
              ]
            }
          ],
